<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8567> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8567" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 735" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2832> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2832" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "These men (called Canuleius and Quintus by Polybius) aided in securing the temporary settlement between Ptolemy VI and Ptolemy VII by which the latter received Cyrene, and in 162 witnessed to this in the Senate (Polyb. 31.10.1-5; cf. Liv. Per. 46; Trogus Prol. 34; Zon. 9.25). See Otto, ABAW 11 (1934) 93f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2831> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2831" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The names and identifications are satisfactory but not certain. See Otto, ABAW 11 (1934) 92f., and note 6." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2680> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2680" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably continued in command in Spain until succeeded by Marcellus in 169 (see 169, Praetors)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2644> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2644" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Placed in charge of proceedings against three of his predecessors for peculation in Spain, he incurred suspicion of collusion when he interrupted the prosecution and went to his province (Liv. 43.2.1-12). He was instructed to found at Carteia a Latin colony of sons of soldiers and native women (43.3.1-4). Cf. Liv. 45.16.1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2643> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2643" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 42.28.5 Provinces and armies 42.31.6-9." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2603> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2603" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Early in 173 these reported the increase in factional strife in Aetolia (Liv. 42.2.1-2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2568> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2568" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to Aetolia to compose serious factional strife there and reported their inability to do so (Liv. 41.25.5-6, and 27.4). See 173, Legates; and on Valerius, Münzer, Gent. Val. 47, no. 36; on Popillius, Münzer, APF 216ff." .
